$interpreted: Devious: Andrew! Finally!
Devious: I've been waiting anxiously~ How'd it go?
Andrew: She agreed.
Andrew: After publicly announcing that she withdraws, both her and Lazer will leave the Desert Kingdom.
Devious: Hsssss. Excellent. Excellent...the sorrows of the desert people will finally come to an end.
Andrew: High Priest, do you really believe I'll win?
Devious: Andrew?
Andrew: If you believed I'd win all along, why attack the Juan family in the middle of the night? It was only because the Juan's believed the Shrine was neutral that they were so easily destroyed.
Devious: ...This is true. The killer was sent by the Shrine.
Devious: But I didn't tell them to set the place on fire, and certainly did not order them to kill anyone!!!!
Andrew: Not everyone. Diana Juan Gomez was the only survivor.
Andrew: The family was burnt to a crisp. The fact that she lived through that fire...
Devious: Pure luck, that's all!
Andrew: Is not luck a sign from the Snake God?
Andrew: When I saw her emerge from the Juan family home, it was hard not to believe she was chosen for the throne.
Devious: The Shrine supports you because you are worthy to be King. We hope you can be a light of hope for the citizens of the desert.
Devious: You will be a great king. Don't think too lowly of yourself.
Andrew: Is that so...
Devious: Is that why instead of killing her on the spot, you chose to protect her?
Andrew: ......
Devious: Let me save you from your wavering.
Devious: After the proclamation ceremony, when she's leaving the desert, I'll let her rest in peace forever. No one will ever know...
Clover: ......
Lazer: I told you that you were naive. If you don't die, Andrew will always feel uneasy.
Lazer: They won't let you go.
Clover: I...
Lazer: You didn't believe me when I said it. Now that you've heard it from Andrew's own mouth, you'd best believe.
Shrine Guard: Where's the rat? Who dares sneak into the Shrine?
Shrine Guard: Got 'em!
Devious: What was that...who's there?
Lazer: If we don't leave, we're dead! Let's go!

You will be a great king. Don't think too lowly of yourself.
Is that so...
Is that why instead of killing her on the spot, you chose to protect her?
Let me save you from your wavering.
After the proclamation ceremony, when she's leaving the desert, I'll let her rest in peace forever. No one will ever know...
I told you that you were naive. If you don't die, Andrew will always feel uneasy.
They won't let you go.
You didn't believe me when I said it. Now that you've heard it from Andrew's own mouth, you'd best believe.
Where's the rat? Who dares sneak into the Shrine?
Got 'em!
What was that...who's there?
If we don't leave, we're dead! Let's go!
